Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; slice crosswise into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄4-inch-thick pieces (halve lengthwise first if carrots are on the larger side).

Toss zucchini and carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @olive oil{1%tablespoon}, @za'atar spice{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{18-22%minutes}.

> For easy cleanup, line sheet with aluminum foil first.

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, 1 cup water, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Peel and mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}; reserve a pinch in a #small bowl{}. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

To bowl with reserved garlic, add @sour cream{3%tablespoon} and a pinch of lemon zest. Add water 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and a pinch of salt; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce}, @Turkish spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and remaining garlic. Cook, breaking meat up into pieces, until beef is cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

> Near the end of cooking, stir in a splash of water and scrape up browned bits from bottom of pan to ensure beef is saucy and flavorful!

Fluff couscous with a #fork{}; stir in roasted veggies, a squeeze of lemon juice, and a drizzle of olive oil. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

Divide couscous between bowls; top with beef. Drizzle with sauce and garnish with @sliced almonds{1/2%ounce} and scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.